Subject: [PATCH] feat(voice): pre-rec TRAI disclosure + AES-256-GCM call
 recordings

- main.py on_call_start now loads pre-recorded disclosure WAV from
  assets/ (falls back to runtime TTS if missing). Saves ~500ms latency
  + Sarvam credits per inbound call.
- New JovioAgent.save_recording: encrypts call audio with AES-256-GCM
  (12-byte nonce + ciphertext+tag) and uploads to Supabase storage at
  recordings/<tenant_id>/<call_id>.wav.enc.
- New SupabaseClient.upload_recording helper.
- Per-tenant keys supported via JOVIO_RECORDING_KEY_<uuid>; global
  JOVIO_RECORDING_KEY fallback.
- cryptography>=42.0.0 added to requirements.
- env example: JOVIO_RECORDING_KEY + SUPABASE_RECORDINGS_BUCKET.
- New: scripts/generate_trai_disclosure.py (pre-records WAVs for 3 voices).
- New: voice-pipeline/assets/README.md.
